Reasoning: The paper presents methods for generating sparse roadmap spanners for joint-based robotic planning, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of optimization techniques and random sampling suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the L1-norm metric function, which is commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the benefits of pre-computing the roadmap offline, which is relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
